params.name: images
params.description: Image to preprocess. Expects a single or batch of images with pixel values ranging from 0 to 255. Ifpassing in images with pixel values between 0 and 1, set do_rescale=False.

params.name: image_mean
params.description: Mean to use if normalizing the image. Can be a float or a list of floats corresponding to the number of channels in the image.

params.name: image_std
params.description: Standard deviation to use if normalizing the image. Can be a float or a list of floats corresponding to the number of channels in the image.

params.name: return_tensors
params.description: The type of tensors to return. Can be one of:Unset: Return a list of np.ndarray.TensorType.TENSORFLOW or tf: Return a batch of type tf.Tensor.TensorType.PYTORCH or pt: Return a batch of type torch.Tensor.TensorType.NUMPY or np: Return a batch of type np.ndarray.TensorType.JAX or jax: Return a batch of type jax.numpy.ndarray.
